00:52:17  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_5.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Rocket Manifest — Attempt 5\n\n## Attempt 4 failure analysis\n- **Failure mode:** loss of attitude control immediately after first-stage separation; upper stage tumbled and re-entered/fell back to Kerbin.\n- **Telemetry / indication:** operator reported successful first-stage ascent and successful stage separation, followed by **immediate uncontrollable tumbling** of the final stage.\n- **Specific telemetry reading indicating the fault:** while the exact 5-second log line was not provided, the failure occurred at the stage transition point after a successful Kerbin ascent, indicating an attitude-control/stability issue rather than a delta-v shortfall.\n- **Root cause:** the upper stage is very small and aerodynamically/moment-arm unstable during near-atmospheric staging. Without fins on the booster and with only a small probe core plus inline stabilizer on the upper stage, separation likely occurred while dynamic pressure was still high enough to induce rapid flipping. The script also immediately attempts to continue guidance without an explicit post-separation stabilization hold.\n- **Correction in Attempt 5:** revise both vehicle and script. Add aerodynamic stability to the lower stage and increase upper-stage control authority. Specifically add four fins to the booster and a larger reaction wheel to the upper stage. The script will also delay upper-stage ignition until attitude is stabilized after separation and will keep the ascent more prograde / less aggressive through the denser atmosphere.\n\n## Mission target\nLaunch from Kerbin and achieve a stable Mun orbit with periapsis >= 10 km and apoapsis <= 500 km, sustained for one full Mun orbit without thrust.\n\n## Sources used\n- kRPC ascent/autopilot guidance references.\n- KSP wiki / indexed metadata for exact stock part names.\n- Community delta-v map / cheat sheet for mission budget.\n\n## Exact part list (top to bottom)\n1. `Probodobodyne OKTO2`\n2. `Advanced Reaction Wheel Module, Large`\n3. `FL-T100 Fuel Tank`\n4. `FL-T400 Fuel Tank`\n5. `LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine`\n6. `TD-12 Decoupler`\n7. `FL-T800 Fuel Tank`\n8. `FL-T800 Fuel Tank`\n9. `FL-T400 Fuel Tank`\n10. `LV-T45 "Swivel" Liquid Fuel Engine`\n11. `AV-R8 Winglet` x4 mounted symmetrically near the base of the first stage\n12. Launch clamps as needed for pad stability\n\n## Stage table\n| Stage | Purpose | Exact active parts | Decoupler placement | Ignition mass (t) | Burnout mass before separation (t) | Isp used | Delta-v (m/s) | TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch, gravity turn, set Kerbin apoapsis to 80–100 km | `LV-T45 "Swivel" Liquid Fuel Engine` + `FL-T800 Fuel Tank` + `FL-T800 Fuel Tank` + `FL-T400 Fuel Tank` + `AV-R8 Winglet` x4 | `TD-12 Decoupler` directly above first-stage tanks | 15.04 | 3.79 | 285 s effective ascent average | 3845 | 1.36 at Kerbin sea level |\n| 2 | Circularization, TMI, Mun corrections, MOI | `LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine` + `FL-T400 Fuel Tank` + `FL-T100 Fuel Tank` + `Advanced Reaction Wheel Module, Large` + `Probodobodyne OKTO2` | No additional decoupler; terminal stage | 3.74 | 1.04 | 345 s vacuum | 4335 | 1.64 in vacuum |\n\n## Total performance\n- **Total delta-v:** **8180 m/s**\n- **Required minimum:** **5250 m/s**\n- **Margin above requirement:** **2930 m/s**\n\n## Calculation notes\n### Stage 2\nApproximate stock-value calculation with added large reaction wheel:\n- wet mass = 3.74 t\n- dry mass = 1.04 t\n- Isp = 345 s\n- thrust = 60 kN\n- delta-v ≈ **4335 m/s**\n- vacuum TWR ≈ **1.64**\n\n### Stage 1\nApproximate stock-value calculation with four winglets:\n- launch mass = 15.04 t\n- burnout mass before separation = 3.79 t\n- effective ascent Isp = 285 s\n- sea-level thrust = 200 kN\n- delta-v ≈ **3845 m/s**\n- launch TWR ≈ **1.36**\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / torque sources:**\n  - `Probodobodyne OKTO2`\n  - `Advanced Reaction Wheel Module, Large` on the upper stage\n  - engine gimbal on the `LV-T45 "Swivel" Liquid Fuel Engine`\n- **RCS:** not installed\n\n## Decoupler and staging plan\n- `TD-12 Decoupler` separates the upper stage from the first stage.\n- VAB stage order should be:\n  1. Ignite `LV-T45 "Swivel" Liquid Fuel Engine`\n  2. Decouple empty first stage via `TD-12 Decoupler`\n  3. Ignite `LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine`\n\n## Placement notes\n- Mount the four `AV-R8 Winglet` parts in 4-way symmetry near the bottom of the first-stage `FL-T400 Fuel Tank`, just above the engine.\n- The `Advanced Reaction Wheel Module, Large` is directly below the `Probodobodyne OKTO2` and above the upper-stage fuel tanks.\n- Keep the rocket perfectly inline and symmetric.\n\n## Build notes for operator\n- Rebuild to this revised manifest; this is not the same as Attempt 4.\n- Do not add extra boosters or change staging beyond what is listed.\n- Use launch clamps only for pad stability.\n'})
