01:52:51  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_3.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 3\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 2\n**Failure mode:** staging/control logic failure after second-stage depletion; final stage was not used and the mission coasted in Kerbin orbit until abort.\n\n**Telemetry evidence:**\n- Operator report: *"After depleting fuel, we did not utilize the final stage and orbited Kerbin twice prior to mission abort."*\n- Logged telemetry shows long coasting with remaining fuel and no successful progression to TMI/MOI logic.\n- The script also showed pathological ascent/circularization behavior in later reruns, indicating the control logic was too brittle.\n\n**Root cause:** primarily **flight script staging/phase logic**, not insufficient delta-v. The vehicle family has enough budget, but the script did not robustly detect stage depletion / engine transitions and its ascent-node logic was unstable.\n\n## Design change philosophy for Attempt 3\nKeep the rocket **simple, high-thrust, 2-stage**, so the script only needs to handle one major separation before orbit operations.\n\nThis reduces failure points dramatically:\n- one atmospheric booster stage\n- one vacuum transfer/capture stage\n- no reliance on a third stage being recognized correctly\n\n## Planned mission architecture\n- **Stage 1:** powerful launch/ascent stage using **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** on a large 2.5 m tank stack.\n- **Stage 2:** single **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** with large fuel reserve for circularization, TMI, and MOI.\n\n## Sources consulted\n- KSP stock exact part names from KSP wiki / mirrored stock tables.\n- Community delta-v map / cheat sheet: surface to LKO ~3400 m/s, LKO to Mun intercept ~860 m/s, Mun orbit insertion ~310 m/s.\n- Standard stock KSP 1.x values used for planning:\n  - **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**: 1500 kN thrust, Isp 285 s ASL / 310 s vac, mass 6.0 t.\n  - **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**: 250 kN thrust, Isp 90 s ASL / 350 s vac, mass 1.75 t.\n  - **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**: wet 18.0 t, dry 2.0 t.\n  - **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**: wet 9.0 t, dry 1.0 t.\n\n## FINAL BUILD TO USE (top to bottom)\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n5. **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n6. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n7. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n8. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n10. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** mounted near base of first stage\n11. **4 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** as needed for rigidity\n12. **3 x TT-18A Launch Stability Enhancer** on pad\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / attitude control:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod** reaction wheel\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** directly below pod\n- **RCS:** **None**\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** directly between the upper Poodle stage and the lower Mainsail stage.\n\n## Stage Table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing Order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Tanks | Decoupler placement | Est. ΔV | Est. TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch / gravity turn / bulk ascent | **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25 Decoupler** above Stage 1 | ~3,250 m/s | **~2.10** |\n| 2 | Circularization / TMI / MOI / reserve | **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **1 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | none | ~2,500 m/s | ~2.1 vacuum |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~5,750 m/s**\n\n## Approximate mass model\n- Mk1 Command Pod: 0.84 t\n- Mk16 Parachute: 0.10 t\n- Advanced Inline Stabilizer: 0.20 t\n- Upper stage tank: Rockomax X200-16 = 9.0 t wet / 1.0 t dry\n- Poodle: 1.75 t\n- TD-25 Decoupler: ~0.3 t\n- Lower stage tanks: 2 x Rockomax X200-32 = 36.0 t wet / 4.0 t dry\n- Mainsail: 6.0 t\n- Fins/struts allowance: ~0.3 t\n\nApproximate launch mass ≈ **54.5 t**\n\n### Launch TWR check\n`1500 / (54.5 * 9.81) ≈ 2.81`\n\nEven with mass uncertainty and aero drag, this is comfortably above the required **1.3**.\n\n## Why this manifest is preferable\n- Only **one** decoupler event before orbit operations.\n- Very strong first stage means the script can use a straightforward gravity turn and still reach a parking orbit.\n- Large Poodle upper stage gives enough margin to perform all vacuum mission phases without depending on precise leftover fractions from a tiny third stage.\n\n## Operator notes\n- Build exactly as listed in **FINAL BUILD TO USE**.\n- Standard staging:\n  1. Launch clamps + Mainsail ignition\n  2. Decouple empty first stage / ignite Poodle stage\n  3. Parachute only for any later recovery use\n- No manual steering during flight.\n- No fuel priority edits.\n\n## Uncertainty note\nDirect official wiki fetches were partially blocked during this run, so numeric values are grounded in standard stock KSP 1.x values and mirrored stock tables. Exact part names in this manifest are stock-valid and should match the VAB.'})
