02:02:59  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_4.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 4\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 3\n**Failure mode:** insufficiently precise circularization guidance.\n\n**Telemetry / operator evidence:**\n- Reported exception: `RuntimeError: Failed circularization: PE=65654 BODY=Kerbin`\n- This indicates Phase 2 missed the required periapsis threshold of 75 km by about **9.3 km**.\n\n**Root cause:** primarily **guidance and burn-termination logic**, not rocket performance. The vehicle reached near-orbit, but the script’s one-shot circularization estimate and execution were too brittle.\n\n## Design strategy for Attempt 4\nUse a rocket that is still simple but gives **more vacuum burn authority and margin** so the guidance can use iterative closed-loop corrections instead of a single brittle node solution.\n\nThis manifest intentionally favors:\n- very strong first stage for easy ascent\n- large upper stage with high thrust and deep reserves\n- only **one major separation event** before orbit operations\n\n## FINAL BUILD TO USE (top to bottom)\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n5. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n6. **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n7. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n8. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n10. **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n11. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** on the lower stage\n12. **4 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** for rigidity as needed\n13. **3 x TT-18A Launch Stability Enhancer** on pad\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / control:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod** reaction wheel\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** directly below pod\n- **RCS:** **None required**\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** between the upper Poodle stage and lower Mainsail stage.\n\n## Stage Table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing Order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Tanks | Decoupler placement | Est. ΔV | Est. TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch / gravity turn / near-orbit insertion | **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25** above first stage | ~2,950 m/s | **~1.88** |\n| 2 | Circularization / TMI / MOI / correction reserve | **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | none | ~3,150 m/s | ~1.35 vacuum early / rises through burn |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~6,100 m/s**\n\n## Approximate mass model\n- Mk1 Command Pod: 0.84 t\n- Mk16 Parachute: 0.10 t\n- Advanced Inline Stabilizer: 0.20 t\n- Upper stage tanks: 2 x Rockomax X200-16 = 18.0 t wet / 2.0 t dry\n- Poodle: 1.75 t\n- TD-25 Decoupler: ~0.3 t\n- Lower stage tanks: 2 x Rockomax X200-32 = 36.0 t wet / 4.0 t dry\n- Mainsail: 6.0 t\n- Fins/struts allowance: ~0.3 t\n\nApproximate launch mass ≈ **63.5 t**\n\n### Launch TWR check\n`1500 / (63.5 * 9.81) ≈ 2.41`\n\nThis remains safely above the **1.3** minimum.\n\n## Why this should help\n- The upper stage now has enough thrust and fuel to tolerate iterative circularization and correction burns.\n- The mission no longer depends on hitting an exact single burn solution on the first attempt.\n- The same upper stage can perform circularization, transfer, and capture with margin for script corrections.\n\n## Sources consulted\n- KSP stock part names from stock wiki / mirrors.\n- Community delta-v map / cheat sheet for Kerbin → Mun orbit budget.\n- Standard stock KSP 1.x engine/tank figures used in planning:\n  - **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n  - **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n  - **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n  - **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n\n## Operator notes\n- Build exactly as listed above.\n- Standard staging:\n  1. Launch clamps + Mainsail ignition\n  2. Decouple Stage 1 and ignite Poodle upper stage\n  3. No further decouplers\n- No manual steering or tuning during flight.\n\n## Uncertainty note\nDirect official wiki fetches were partially blocked during this run, so numerical values are grounded in standard stock KSP 1.x values and mirrored stock part tables. Exact part names above are stock-valid.'})
