02:16:59  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_5.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 5\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 4\n**Failure mode:** TMI overshoot; vessel missed the Mun and escaped Kerbin into solar orbit.\n\n**Operator evidence:**\n- *"You overshot the moon and went into solar orbit."*\n- *"Rocket launch was great."*\n- *"It seems your fuel accounting is not taking advantage of the kRPC hooks, and you are not navigating to the moon\'s actual position."*\n\n**Root cause:** the ascent vehicle was adequate, but the **transfer guidance was too naive**. The script used an open-loop prograde burn until any encounter-like condition rather than using kRPC’s predictive orbit hooks robustly enough. The transfer burn needed to be **planned against the actual projected orbit / encounter state**, not just phase angle and continuous prograde thrust.\n\n## Design choice for final attempt\nKeep the strong, proven ascent stack from Attempt 4 because launch performance was reported as good. Focus the final revision on the **flight script**, not radical rocket redesign.\n\n## FINAL BUILD TO USE (same hardware class as Attempt 4)\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n5. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n6. **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n7. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n8. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n10. **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n11. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** on lower stage\n12. **4 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** as needed\n13. **3 x TT-18A Launch Stability Enhancer**\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / control:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod** reaction wheel\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** directly under pod\n- **RCS:** **None**\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** between the Poodle upper stage and Mainsail lower stage.\n\n## Stage Table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing Order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Tanks | Decoupler placement | Est. ΔV | Est. TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch / gravity turn / near-orbit insertion | **Rockomax "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25** above first stage | ~2,950 m/s | **~1.88** |\n| 2 | Circularization / TMI / Mun capture / reserve | **RE-I5 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | none | ~3,150 m/s | ~1.35 vacuum early / rises as mass drops |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~6,100 m/s**\n\n## Why the manifest is unchanged\n- Launch and ascent were already validated as good by the operator.\n- The failure was specifically in **navigation / transfer execution**, not in thrust, staging, or delta-v shortage.\n- Keeping the same rocket isolates the final attempt to a script-level fix using better kRPC predictive APIs.\n\n## Sources consulted\n- KSP stock part names from stock wiki / mirrors.\n- Community delta-v map / cheat sheet for Kerbin → Mun orbit budget.\n- Standard stock KSP 1.x values for Mainsail, Poodle, Rockomax X200-32, and Rockomax X200-16.\n\n## Operator notes\n- Build exactly as listed above.\n- Standard staging:\n  1. Launch clamps + Mainsail ignition\n  2. Decouple first stage / ignite Poodle stage\n- No manual steering during flight.\n\n## Uncertainty note\nOfficial wiki fetches were partially blocked during this run, so numeric values are grounded in standard stock KSP 1.x stock values and mirrored part tables. Exact part names above are stock-valid.'})
