02:41:39  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_7.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 7\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 6\n**Failure mode:** Missed the Mun after Trans-Mun Injection; spacecraft passed through the Mun’s orbital region but did not enter the Mun SOI.\n\n**Operator report:**\n- “Attempt failed. Flew past mun.”\n- “While in the correct general direction, perhaps not exactly correct, and probably some discrepancy between your calculated delta-V from the old avail docs and current version.”\n- “Telemetry up to the coast phase logged.”\n\n## Specific diagnosis\nThe vehicle had enough performance to reach the Mun’s orbital distance, so this was **not primarily a launch TWR or total ΔV failure**. The likely failure was **transfer targeting precision**:\n1. The script planned TMI from a coarse grid around a Hohmann estimate.\n2. That coarse search was enough to get near the Mun’s orbit, but not enough to guarantee SOI capture.\n3. A small error in burn timing or burn magnitude at Kerbin escape scales into a large positional miss at Mun distance.\n\n## Root cause\n**Guidance / burn targeting error**, not a hardware shortfall.\n\nTo improve probability of success, this attempt keeps the same simple, high-margin launcher but preserves extra upper-stage reserve for a more aggressive and more precise TMI search / correction strategy in the script.\n\n---\n\n## Exact parts list\nBuild exactly in this top-to-bottom stack order:\n\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n5. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n6. **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n7. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n8. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n10. **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n11. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** on lower stage\n12. **4 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** reinforcing stack as needed\n13. **3 x TT18-A Launch Stability Enhancer**\n\n---\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / reaction wheels:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod**\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** on upper stage\n- **RCS:** none\n- **Monopropellant:** none\n\n---\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** between the upper Poodle stage and the lower Mainsail stage.\n\n---\n\n## Stage table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Propellant tanks | Decoupler placement | Estimated ΔV | Estimated TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch, gravity turn, bulk of ascent | **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25** separates to upper stage | ~2,900 m/s | ~1.85 at Kerbin sea level |\n| 2 | Orbit insertion, TMI, course correction, MOI | **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | none | ~3,150 m/s | ~0.95 in vacuum at ignition |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~6,050 m/s**\n\nThis remains above the required **5,250 m/s** threshold.\n\n---\n\n## Why the rocket remains unchanged\n- Prior attempts demonstrate the stack can reach stable Kerbin orbit.\n- The failure mode was a **targeting miss at interbody scale**, not inadequate propellant.\n- Retaining the same vehicle isolates the fix to mission logic and avoids introducing new ascent/staging risks.\n\n---\n\n## Operator build notes\n- Build exactly as listed.\n- Set VAB staging as:\n  1. Launch clamps release + Mainsail ignition\n  2. TD-25 decouple + Poodle ignition\n  3. Parachute separate stage only\n- No manual steering or correction during flight.\n- Connect kRPC before running the script.\n\n---\n\n## Grounding note\nExact part names are stock-valid KSP 1.x names. Performance estimates are conservative stock planning values cross-checked against accessible KSP wiki mirrors / community tables, with the official KSP wiki partially blocked by anti-bot protection during this session.'})
