02:49:49  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_8.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 8\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 7\n**Failure mode:** TMI underperformance — the spacecraft was on the correct orbital heading but could not add enough velocity to turn the parking orbit into a Mun intercept.\n\n**Operator report:**\n- “Almost the exact same outcome as before.”\n- “You are actually spot on the orbit, but you cannot accelerate enough to intercept.”\n\n## Specific diagnosis\nThis report indicates the **guidance geometry is now close enough**, but the vehicle lacks practical upper-stage transfer performance in the current game setup for:\n- circularization,\n- full TMI,\n- and Mun capture reserve.\n\nSo unlike attempts 6 and 7, the dominant limitation is now **vehicle capability**, specifically **upper-stage effective ΔV / burn authority** rather than aiming logic.\n\n## Root cause\n**Insufficient usable upper-stage performance for the required TMI**, likely due to a mismatch between assumed stock engine/tank performance and the actual installed game/version/mod state.\n\n## Design revision for Attempt 8\nMove to a **higher-energy three-stage launcher**:\n1. Large first stage for atmospheric ascent.\n2. Dedicated vacuum transfer stage for orbital insertion + most of TMI.\n3. Separate lightweight Mun-orbit stage for final transfer trim and MOI.\n\nThis reduces the mass being pushed during TMI and increases effective delivered ΔV.\n\n---\n\n## Exact parts list\nBuild exactly in this top-to-bottom stack order:\n\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **FL-T400 Fuel Tank**\n5. **FL-T400 Fuel Tank**\n6. **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n7. **TD-12 Decoupler**\n8. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n10. **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n11. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n12. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n13. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n14. **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n15. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** on lower stage\n16. **6 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** reinforcing the central stack as needed\n17. **3 x TT18-A Launch Stability Enhancer**\n\n---\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / reaction control:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod** reaction wheel\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** directly below pod\n- **RCS:** none\n- **Monopropellant:** none\n\n---\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-12 Decoupler** between the Terrier Mun-orbit stage and the Poodle transfer stage.\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** between the Poodle transfer stage and the Mainsail launch stage.\n\n---\n\n## Stage table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Propellant tanks | Decoupler placement | Estimated ΔV | Estimated TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch, gravity turn, bulk ascent | **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25** above stage 1 | ~2,700 m/s | ~1.70–1.85 at Kerbin sea level |\n| 2 | Finish ascent, circularization, most of TMI | **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | **TD-12** above stage 2 | ~2,000 m/s | ~0.75–0.90 in vacuum |\n| 3 | TMI trim, Mun capture, large reserve | **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x FL-T400 Fuel Tank** | none | ~1,900 m/s | ~0.45 in vacuum at ignition |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~6,600 m/s**\n\nThis exceeds the required **5,250 m/s** mission minimum with substantial margin.\n\n---\n\n## Why this redesign should solve the reported problem\n- The prior design forced the same upper stage to do everything while still carrying more dead mass during the later mission.\n- A dedicated lightweight **Terrier final stage** dramatically improves vacuum efficiency for final transfer trim and Mun Orbit Insertion.\n- The **Poodle middle stage** can now focus on orbit completion and the majority of the Kerbin-escape burn.\n\n---\n\n## VAB staging order\nSet staging exactly as follows:\n\n### Stage 0\n- **TT18-A Launch Stability Enhancer** release\n- **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 1\n- **TD-25 Decoupler**\n- **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 2\n- **TD-12 Decoupler**\n- **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 3\n- **Mk16 Parachute** only\n\n---\n\n## Operator build notes\n- Keep the stack perfectly inline.\n- Put the four AV-T1 winglets symmetrically on the bottom stage.\n- Use struts to reduce flex between stages.\n- No radial boosters.\n- No manual control during flight.\n- Launch only once kRPC is connected and the vessel is the active pad craft.\n\n---\n\n## Grounding note\nExact part names are stock-valid KSP 1.x names. Performance estimates are planning values based on accessible KSP wiki mirrors / community tables because some official wiki pages were anti-bot protected during this session.'})
