03:18:30  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_9.md', 'content': '# Mun Orbit Mission Manifest — Attempt 9\n\n## Failure analysis from Attempt 8\n**Failure mode 1:** Incorrect staging logic during in-flight execution — the middle stage did not separate when expected.\n\n**Failure mode 2:** Even after reaching the Mun, the script did not execute Mun Orbit Insertion and instead only flew by the Mun.\n\n**Operator report:**\n- “I triple checked. Setup exactly as you asked.”\n- “second stage did not separate.”\n- “There was not attempt to navigate to the munar orbit. Just fly to the mun”\n\n## Specific diagnosis\nTwo distinct software issues were exposed:\n1. **Stage numbering assumptions in the script were wrong.** The code inferred stage identities by hard-coded decouple-stage numbers, but actual in-game stage/resource indexing did not match those assumptions.\n2. **Mun encounter handling relied too much on `next_orbit` / SOI-change assumptions.** The craft reached the Mun, but the script failed to robustly transition from transfer logic into MOI burn execution.\n\n## Root cause\nPrimarily **script staging / event-detection failure**, not rocket insufficiency.\n\n## Design choice for Attempt 9\nKeep the successful high-margin **three-stage vehicle** from Attempt 8, because the operator confirmed the physical build was correct and the craft could at least fly to the Mun. Fix the script to:\n- avoid hard-coded stage indexes,\n- use thrust loss as the trigger to stage,\n- perform MOI whenever the vessel is in Mun SOI or at Mun periapsis on a flyby,\n- enforce explicit phase transitions with clearer failure checks.\n\n---\n\n## Exact parts list\nBuild exactly in this top-to-bottom stack order:\n\n1. **Mk1 Command Pod**\n2. **Mk16 Parachute**\n3. **Advanced Inline Stabilizer**\n4. **FL-T400 Fuel Tank**\n5. **FL-T400 Fuel Tank**\n6. **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n7. **TD-12 Decoupler**\n8. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n9. **Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank**\n10. **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine**\n11. **TD-25 Decoupler**\n12. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n13. **Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank**\n14. **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine**\n15. **4 x AV-T1 Winglet** on lower stage\n16. **6 x EAS-4 Strut Connector** reinforcing the stack as needed\n17. **3 x TT18-A Launch Stability Enhancer**\n\n---\n\n## SAS / RCS specification\n- **SAS / reaction control:**\n  - **Mk1 Command Pod** reaction wheel\n  - **Advanced Inline Stabilizer** under the pod\n- **RCS:** none\n- **Monopropellant:** none\n\n---\n\n## Decoupler placement\n- **TD-12 Decoupler** between Terrier final stage and Poodle transfer stage.\n- **TD-25 Decoupler** between Poodle transfer stage and Mainsail launch stage.\n\n---\n\n## Stage table (order of firing)\n\n| Firing order | Purpose | Engine(s) | Propellant tanks | Decoupler placement | Estimated ΔV | Estimated TWR at ignition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Launch, gravity turn, bulk ascent | **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-32 Fuel Tank** | **TD-25** above stage 1 | ~2,700 m/s | ~1.70–1.85 at Kerbin sea level |\n| 2 | Finish ascent, circularization, TMI | **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x Rockomax X200-16 Fuel Tank** | **TD-12** above stage 2 | ~2,000 m/s | ~0.75–0.90 in vacuum |\n| 3 | Mun capture, circularization, reserve | **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine** | **2 x FL-T400 Fuel Tank** | none | ~1,900 m/s | ~0.45 in vacuum |\n\n**Total planned ΔV:** **~6,600 m/s**\n\n---\n\n## VAB staging order\nPlease set staging exactly like this:\n\n### Stage 0\n- **TT18-A Launch Stability Enhancer** release\n- **RE-M3 "Mainsail" Liquid Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 1\n- **TD-25 Decoupler**\n- **RE-L10 "Poodle" Liquid Fuel Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 2\n- **TD-12 Decoupler**\n- **LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine** ignition\n\n### Stage 3\n- **Mk16 Parachute** only\n\n---\n\n## Operator notes\n- Same hardware as Attempt 8.\n- No manual controls during flight.\n- kRPC connected before running script.\n- This attempt focuses entirely on correcting staging detection and forcing a proper Mun Orbit Insertion burn instead of a flyby.\n\n---\n\n## Grounding note\nExact part names are stock-valid KSP 1.x names. Performance numbers are planning estimates from accessible stock references and community mirrors where official wiki pages were blocked during this session.'})
