15:30:48  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'manifest_attempt_1.md', 'content': '# Rocket Manifest — Attempt 1\n\n## Vehicle Summary\n\nA 3-stage liquid fuel rocket designed for the Kerbin → Mun orbit mission.\nTotal vacuum dV target: ≥ 5,250 m/s.\n\n## Part List\n\n### Command / Recovery\n- Mk1 Command Pod (mass 0.84 t)\n- Mk16 Parachute (mass 0.1 t)\n- TR-18A Stack Decoupler (mass 0.05 t) — between pod and stage 3\n\n### Stage 3 (Upper / Vacuum) — LV-909 "Terrier"\n- TR-18A Stack Decoupler (mass 0.05 t) — between stage 2 and stage 3\n- FL-T400 Fuel Tank (mass 2.25 t full, 0.25 t dry; 400 LF + 400 OX units)\n- LV-909 "Terrier" Liquid Fuel Engine (mass 0.5 t, vac thrust 60 kN, vac Isp 345 s, sea-level Isp 85 s)\n- Total stage 3 dry mass: 0.05 + 0.25 + 0.5 = 0.80 t\n- Total stage 3 wet mass: 0.05 + 2.25 + 0.5 = 2.80 t\n- Stage 3 propellant mass: 2.0 t\n\n### Stage 2 (Sustainer) — LV-T45 "Swivel"\n- TR-18A Stack Decoupler (mass 0.05 t) — between stage 1 and stage 2\n- FL-T800 Fuel Tank (mass 4.5 t full, 0.5 t dry; 800 LF + 800 OX units)\n- LV-T45 "Swivel" Liquid Fuel Engine (mass 1.5 t, vac thrust 215 kN, vac Isp 320 s, sea-level Isp 250 s, gimbal 3°)\n- Total stage 2 dry mass: 0.05 + 0.5 + 1.5 = 2.05 t\n- Total stage 2 wet mass: 0.05 + 4.5 + 1.5 = 6.05 t\n- Stage 2 propellant mass: 4.0 t\n\n### Stage 1 (Booster) — LV-T30 "Reliant"\n- TR-18A Stack Decoupler (mass 0.05 t) — between launch clamps and stage 1\n- 2× FL-T800 Fuel Tank (mass 9.0 t full, 1.0 t dry total; 1600 LF + 1600 OX units total)\n- LV-T30 "Reliant" Liquid Fuel Engine (mass 1.25 t, vac thrust 240 kN, vac Isp 310 s, sea-level Isp 265 s, no gimbal)\n- Total stage 1 dry mass: 0.05 + 1.0 + 1.25 = 2.30 t\n- Total stage 1 wet mass: 0.05 + 9.0 + 1.25 = 10.30 t\n- Stage 1 propellant mass: 8.0 t\n\n## Mass Stacking (Launch Configuration)\n\n| Component | Mass (t) |\n|---|---|\n| Mk1 Command Pod | 0.84 |\n| Mk16 Parachute | 0.10 |\n| TR-18A (pod-stage3) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 3 wet | 2.80 |\n| TR-18A (stage3-stage2) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 2 wet | 6.05 |\n| TR-18A (stage2-stage1) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 1 wet | 10.30 |\n| **Total launch mass** | **20.24 t** |\n\n## Delta-V Calculations (Vacuum Isp)\n\nUsing Tsiolkovsky rocket equation: dV = Isp * g0 * ln(m0/m1), where g0 = 9.81 m/s²\n\n### Stage 3 (vacuum)\n- Isp = 345 s (vacuum)\n- m0 = 2.80 t (stage 3 wet + payload above)\n- Payload above stage 3: Mk1 Pod (0.84) + Mk16 Chute (0.10) + TR-18A (0.05) = 0.99 t\n- Total m0 for stage 3 burn: 2.80 + 0.99 = 3.79 t\n- m1 = 0.80 + 0.99 = 1.79 t\n- dV3 = 345 * 9.81 * ln(3.79/1.79) = 345 * 9.81 * 0.750 = **2,538 m/s**\n\n### Stage 2 (vacuum)\n- Isp = 320 s (vacuum)\n- m0 = 6.05 t (stage 2 wet) + payload above (stage 3 dry + pod + chute + decouplers)\n- Payload above stage 2: stage 3 dry (0.80) + TR-18A (0.05) + pod (0.84) + chute (0.10) + TR-18A (0.05) = 1.84 t\n- Total m0 for stage 2 burn: 6.05 + 1.84 = 7.89 t\n- m1 = 2.05 + 1.84 = 3.89 t\n- dV2 = 320 * 9.81 * ln(7.89/3.89) = 320 * 9.81 * 0.707 = **2,219 m/s**\n\n### Stage 1 (vacuum)\n- Isp = 310 s (vacuum)\n- m0 = 10.30 t (stage 1 wet) + payload above (stage 2 dry + stage 3 dry + pod + chute + decouplers)\n- Payload above stage 1: stage 2 dry (2.05) + TR-18A (0.05) + stage 3 dry (0.80) + TR-18A (0.05) + pod (0.84) + chute (0.10) + TR-18A (0.05) = 3.94 t\n- Total m0 for stage 1 burn: 10.30 + 3.94 = 14.24 t\n- m1 = 2.30 + 3.94 = 6.24 t\n- dV1 = 310 * 9.81 * ln(14.24/6.24) = 310 * 9.81 * 0.826 = **2,512 m/s**\n\n### Total vacuum dV\ndV_total = 2,512 + 2,219 + 2,538 = **7,269 m/s** ✅ (exceeds 5,250 m/s requirement with 38% margin)\n\n## TWR Calculations\n\n### Stage 1 at launch (sea level)\n- Thrust (sea level) = 205.161 kN (from engine table)\n- Mass at launch = 20.24 t\n- TWR = 205.161 / (20.24 * 9.81) = 205.161 / 198.55 = **1.03** ❌ (below 1.3 minimum)\n\nThe TWR is too low! I need to either add more engines or reduce mass. Let me reconsider.\n\n### Revised Stage 1 — Add a second LV-T30\n- 2× LV-T30 "Reliant" (mass 2.50 t total, thrust 410.322 kN sea level)\n- Keep 2× FL-T800 tanks\n- Stage 1 dry mass: 0.05 + 1.0 + 2.50 = 3.55 t\n- Stage 1 wet mass: 0.05 + 9.0 + 2.50 = 11.55 t\n- TWR = 410.322 / (20.24 + 1.25 * 9.81)... wait, the total mass changes.\n\nLet me recalculate with 2× Reliant on stage 1.\n\n**Revised mass stacking:**\n\n| Component | Mass (t) |\n|---|---|\n| Mk1 Command Pod | 0.84 |\n| Mk16 Parachute | 0.10 |\n| TR-18A (pod-stage3) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 3 wet (Terrier + FL-T400) | 2.80 |\n| TR-18A (stage3-stage2) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 2 wet (Swivel + FL-T800) | 6.05 |\n| TR-18A (stage2-stage1) | 0.05 |\n| Stage 1 wet (2×Reliant + 2×FL-T800) | 11.55 |\n| **Total launch mass** | **21.49 t** |\n\nTWR at launch: 2 × 205.161 / (21.49 × 9.81) = 410.322 / 210.82 = **1.95** ✅\n\n### Stage 1 dV (vacuum, 2 engines)\n- Isp = 310 s (vacuum) — same for Reliant\n- m0 = 11.55 + payload above\n- Payload above stage 1: stage 2 dry (2.05) + TR-18A (0.05) + stage 3 dry (0.80) + TR-18A (0.05) + pod (0.84) + chute (0.10) + TR-18A (0.05) = 3.94 t\n- Total m0 = 11.55 + 3.94 = 15.49 t\n- m1 = 3.55 + 3.94 = 7.49 t\n- dV1 = 310 * 9.81 * ln(15.49/7.49) = 310 * 9.81 * 0.727 = **2,211 m/s**\n\n### Revised total dV\ndV_total = 2,211 + 2,219 + 2,538 = **6,968 m/s** ✅ (still well above 5,250)\n\n## Stage Table\n\n| Stage | Engine(s) | Tanks | Decoupler | Wet Mass (t) | Dry Mass (t) | Vac dV (m/s) | TWR (sea level) |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 (booster) | 2× LV-T30 "Reliant" | 2× FL-T800 | TR-18A (below) | 11.55 | 3.55 | 2,211 | 1.95 |\n| 2 (sustainer) | 1× LV-T45 "Swivel" | 1× FL-T800 | TR-18A (below) | 6.05 | 2.05 | 2,219 | — |\n| 3 (vacuum) | 1× LV-909 "Terrier" | 1× FL-T400 | TR-18A (below) | 2.80 | 0.80 | 2,538 | — |\n| **Total** | — | — | — | **21.49** | — | **6,968** | — |\n\n## SAS / Control\n- Mk1 Command Pod contains built-in reaction wheels (sufficient for this rocket)\n- LV-T45 "Swivel" on stage 2 provides 3° gimbal for ascent steering\n- Stage 1 has no gimbal (LV-T30 has 0° gimbal), but differential thrust not needed with 2 engines\n- No RCS thrusters included (not needed for this mission profile)\n- SAS enabled throughout via command pod reaction wheels\n\n## Staging Order\n\n1. **Launch:** Activate stage 1 (2× Reliant engines), throttle to 100%\n2. **Stage 1 separation:** When stage 1 fuel depleted, decouple TR-18A, activate stage 2 (Swivel)\n3. **Stage 2 separation:** When stage 2 fuel depleted (or after LKO circularization), decouple TR-18A, activate stage 3 (Terrier)\n4. **TMI:** Stage 3 performs TMI burn\n5. **MOI:** Stage 3 performs Mun orbit insertion burn\n'})
