17:27:43  INFO      causal_agent.research_planner  |  tool call >> save_file({'filename': 'hypotheses_5.md', 'content': "# Hypotheses — Attempt 5\n\n## Current belief state (based on postmortems 1-4)\n\n**The Skipper + Jumbo-64 first stage is too powerful.** It provides 4,056 m/s vacuum dV, pushing the vessel to 2,618 m/s at 62 km — well above circular orbital speed (2,310 m/s at that altitude). By the time the first stage depletes, the vessel is already on a highly elliptical orbit (AP=726 km) and needs a retrograde burn to circularize.\n\n**New design:** Use a **Skipper + Rockomax X200-32** (smaller tank). This provides 2,976 m/s vacuum dV — enough to reach near-orbit without overshooting. The Terrier then circularizes with a prograde burn.\n\n## Competing hypotheses\n\n### H1: Skipper + X200-32 provides the right amount of first-stage dV\n- Prediction: Skipper burns for ~77 seconds, reaching ALT > 40 km.\n- Prediction: AP at Skipper burnout will be 80-150 km (not escape).\n- Prediction: SPD at burnout will be 1,800-2,200 m/s (below circular speed).\n- Prediction: ECC at burnout < 1.0.\n\n### H2: The Terrier can circularize from the Skipper's burnout state\n- Prediction: Circularization dV will be positive and < 500 m/s.\n- Prediction: The Terrier has enough fuel to circularize.\n- Prediction: PE >= 75 km after circularization.\n\n### H3: The Spark has enough dV for TMI + MOI\n- Prediction: TMI dV ~860 m/s, MOI dV ~310 m/s.\n- Prediction: Spark (1,913 m/s) has enough for both.\n- Prediction: At least 5% fuel remains after MOI.\n\n### H4: Total dV budget is sufficient\n- Total: 2,976 + 1,738 + 1,913 = 6,627 m/s.\n- Atmospheric losses: ~1,200-1,500 m/s.\n- Remaining after LKO: ~2,500-3,000 m/s — enough for TMI + MOI.\n\n## What this experiment tests\n\nThis attempt tests whether reducing the first-stage fuel (Skipper + X200-32 instead of Jumbo-64) provides a better ascent profile where the upper stages can circularize with a prograde burn.\n"})
