17:29:00  INFO      causal_agent.human_interface  |  human_notify: Attempt 5 is ready with a critical design change!

**Problem from A4:** The Skipper + Jumbo-64 (36 t fuel) was too powerful — it pushed the vessel to 2,618 m/s at 62 km (above circular orbital speed), making circularization impossible with a prograde burn.

**Fix:** Reduced first-stage fuel from Jumbo-64 (36 t) to X200-32 (18 t). This gives:
- Stage 1 dV: 2,976 m/s (was 4,056 m/s) — enough to reach orbit without overshooting
- TWR at launch: 2.22 (was 1.31) — much snappier ascent
- Expected AP at burnout: ~80-150 km (not escape)
- Total vacuum dV: 6,627 m/s — still plenty of margin

**Files:**
- hypotheses_5.md
- manifest_attempt_5.md
- flight_attempt_5.py

